## Context

The Transformers.js library supports 27 pipeline types but is missing an `image-text-to-text` pipeline for Vision-Language Models (VLMs) like LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, etc. The model infrastructure already exists — `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (in `src/models.js:8736`) supports 11 architectures (llava, llava_onevision, moondream1, florence2, qwen2-vl, idefics3, smolvlm, paligemma, llava_qwen2, gemma3n, mistral3). What's missing is the pipeline class, its JSDoc types, its SUPPORTED_TASKS registration, and a test file.

Unlike the existing `ImageToTextPipeline` (which takes only images and generates captions), this pipeline accepts **both an image and a text prompt**, enabling conversational VLM interactions like "Describe this image" or "What text is in this image?".

## Changes

All changes are in **one file** (`src/pipelines.js`) plus **one new test file**.

### Step 1: Add import — `src/pipelines.js` line ~44

